<h2>Overview — why this partner is useful</h2>
<p>The strongest case for resilience and equity is easy to nod along to and then quietly ignore when the numbers favor building. This partner makes that case hard to ignore. It will ask who your redesign displaces, whether your green-blue claims hold up against flood and heat data, and whether your affordability story is real. The point is not to obey it any more than you obey the Urban Planner. The point is to <strong>synthesize the two</strong> and name the trade-off you can actually defend in front of a real audience.</p>
<p>One line it holds: protecting people and protecting land are not free either. The Equity &amp; Resilience Partner will press hard for green space and against displacement, and it will also tell you honestly when your caution has quietly priced out the housing a growing city genuinely needs. That honesty is what keeps it a partner rather than a protest sign.</p>

